0.title: Big-O Notation
0.description: Big-O notation is a mathematical notation that describes the limiting behavior of a function when the argument tends towards a particular value or infinity.

1.title: Data Structures Explained
1.description: Data structures are a way of organizing and storing data so that it can be accessed and modified efficiently.

2.title: Data Structures and Algorithms
2.description: Data structures are a way of organizing and storing data so that it can be accessed and modified efficiently.

3.title: Algorithms
3.description: An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for calculations, data processing, and automated reasoning tasks.

data.title: Breadth First Search (BFS)
data.description: Breadth-first search (BFS) is an algorithm for traversing or searching tree or graph data structures.

data.title: Depth First Search (DFS)
data.description: Depth-first search (DFS) is an algorithm for traversing or searching tree or graph data structures.

data.Title: Recursion
data.description: Recursion is a method of solving a problem where the solution depends on solutions to smaller instances of the same problem.

data.title: Dijkstra's Algorithm
data.description: Dijkstra's algorithm is an algorithm for finding the shortest paths between nodes in a graph.

data.title: Dynamic Programming
data.description: Dynamic programming is a method for solving complex problems by breaking them down into simpler subproblems.

data.title: Greedy Algorithms
data.description: Greedy algorithms are a class of algorithms that make locally optimal choices at each stage with the hope of finding a global optimum.

data.title: Backtracking
data.description: Backtracking is an algorithmic technique for solving problems incrementally, one piece at a time.

data.title: Quick Sort
data.description: Quick sort is an efficient sorting algorithm that uses divide-and-conquer principles.

data.Title: Bubble Sort
data.description: Bubble sort is a simple sorting algorithm that repeatedly steps through the list, compares adjacent elements and swaps them if they are in the wrong order.

data.title: Merge Sort
data.description: Merge sort is an efficient, stable, comparison-based, divide and conquer sorting algorithm.

data.title: Heap Sort
data.description: Heap sort is a comparison-based sorting technique based on a binary heap data structure.

data.title: Insertion Sort
data.description: Insertion sort is a simple sorting algorithm that builds a sorted array one element at a time.

data.title: Union Find
data.description: Union-Find is a data structure that keeps track of elements that are split into one or more disjoint sets.
